headline: Cummins (CMI): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Cummins has had an impressive run over the past six months as its shares have beaten the S&P 500 by 20.8%. The stock now trades at $372.27, marking a 33.8% gain. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
